President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to answer questions from MPs  on Thursday. Issues he is expected to address include the government's response to the Covid-19 pandemic, corruption and gender-based violence. His office said Ramaphosa would also touch on the government's plans to reduce inequality, unemployment and poverty. PODCAST | Ramaphosa's open letter against corruption rings hollow Subscribe: iono.fm | Spotify | Apple Podcast | Pocket Casts | Player.fm